Chronic kidney disease stage IIIb likely secondary to hypertensive nephrosclerosis
Review of record reveals serum creatinine trended up to 1.6 after episode of hypertensive emergency with peak creatinine 2.5
Hx of Nsaids use on and off which was stopped a month ago
Electrolyte and acid-base parameters are stable
Rena; US 6/2021 shows R kidney measures 7.9 cm and L kidney measures 8.3 cm
Mild proteinuria noted ACR-85 with UPCR 0.38
SPEP, free light chains unremarkable

Formatting of this note might be different from the original.
Renal function relatively stable
Currently on amlodipine and labetalol for blood pressure control
Check RFP, UPCR, Renal US with dopplerand PTH
Will increase labetalol 200 mg three times in a day
Strict blood pressure control recommended to delay progression
Avoid NSAIDs, IV contrast and Phos containing enemas
Follow in 6 weeks

Blood pressure SBP<130 mmHg DBP<80 mmHg
Blood pressure high in office
Currently on amlodipine and labetalol
Will increase labetalol 200 mg to TID
Will also check Aldo renin ratio along with Renal US doppler.
Low-salt diet and heart healthy recommended
Blood pressure at home and make a log
Calling our office if blood pressure above 140 mmHg

hemoglobin low likely secondary to chronic kidney disease
